HEADWORD: Knebelite
<hw>Kne"bel*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From Major von
<ets>Knebel</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a gray,
red, brown, or green color, and glistening luster. It is a silicate of
iron and manganese.</def>⟦br⟧
